43:23.894 --> 43:26.187
- There's no room.
- Make room.

43:26.646 --> 43:28.105
What happened to necessity?

43:28.565 --> 43:29.940
It just changed!

43:30.192 --> 43:32.109
Not for me. Let's go!

43:32.360 --> 43:35.279
- What if that was you?
- What if this was you without Kevlar?

43:35.447 --> 43:36.864
Hey! Hey.

43:41.870 --> 43:43.537
Great, a fucking tank.

43:43.789 --> 43:45.372
That should send us on our way.

43:47.876 --> 43:49.084
L.A.W., sir?

43:51.213 --> 43:52.588
No, let's get out of here.

43:52.881 --> 43:54.423
It's about fucking time!

43:56.593 --> 43:59.178
Ride in that Humvee. Let's go!
Let's go! In the Humvee.

43:59.387 --> 44:02.056
Come on, sweetheart.
Come on, come on, come on.

44:06.895 --> 44:08.479
Hurry up.

44:10.315 --> 44:11.774
Let's go.

44:32.462 --> 44:34.505
Stupid son of a bitch.
We were home free!

44:34.756 --> 44:36.423
Give me that arm.

44:40.720 --> 44:41.971
What's that tank doing?

44:44.558 --> 44:46.559
I don't know. Looks like it stopped.

45:26.975 --> 45:27.975
Mortar!

45:32.355 --> 45:33.480
It's gas!

45:49.623 --> 45:51.498
Where's my mask?

45:53.293 --> 45:54.877
Where's my fucking mask?

45:58.715 --> 45:59.882
Where's my mask?

46:01.009 --> 46:02.009
Mine!

47:26.886 --> 47:29.263
Hey, stop! Stop!

47:29.597 --> 47:33.058
Hey! Wait! Those are mines!

47:36.229 --> 47:37.938
Come back this way!

47:40.483 --> 47:42.151
Hey, stop!

48:04.674 --> 48:07.426
No, no, no, this isn't sarin.
We'd be dead already.

48:07.594 --> 48:09.970
- What is it, mustard?
- It's C.S. Come on.

48:10.138 --> 48:14.099
- Tear gas?
- Yeah, times 10.

48:18.521 --> 48:21.231
Come here. Come here. Put this on.

48:22.484 --> 48:23.817
Here, you take it.

48:25.445 --> 48:27.362
You see that? That's a mine!
Come here.

48:27.530 --> 48:30.824
Don't step there. Do not step there.
Where's your kids?

48:34.871 --> 48:36.705
Cover your face. Come here.

48:36.956 --> 48:38.999
Where are your children?

48:39.167 --> 48:41.085
What happened to your children?

48:44.839 --> 48:45.839
Watch your back!

48:47.717 --> 48:48.717
Freeze! Don't move!

48:48.968 --> 48:51.303
- What's going on?
- I don't know.

48:56.434 --> 49:00.062
It's okay. They're helping us.
They're with the rebels.

49:00.605 --> 49:02.106
They got a shelter.

49:03.566 --> 49:04.942
Tunnel.

49:09.489 --> 49:11.240
Go, go. Get in!

49:11.491 --> 49:13.492
I gotta look for Barlow.

49:13.701 --> 49:15.077
Where's Troy?

49:15.328 --> 49:17.538
Wait a minute! Where's Troy?

49:17.705 --> 49:20.499
Hey, man. We gotta get out of here.

49:21.042 --> 49:22.042
Where is Troy?

49:22.293 --> 49:23.961
- Come on!
- Get off me!

49:25.213 --> 49:26.630
Let's go.

49:30.844 --> 49:34.805
You motherfucker.
Get the fuck off me!

49:45.733 --> 49:47.734
Barlow?

49:48.653 --> 49:50.320
Barlow?

50:31.654 --> 50:33.989
Get the fuck off me.

50:35.450 --> 50:37.784
We have to go back and get Troy.

50:37.952 --> 50:40.287
He's not out there.
We have to wait till it clears.

50:40.455 --> 50:42.831
You made a choice in the village
and we lost Troy.

50:43.124 --> 50:45.042
- I had no choice.
- You had a choice!

50:45.293 --> 50:47.502
I had no choice.

50:48.880 --> 50:52.549
What about Troy?
What choice does he have now?

51:46.396 --> 51:48.272
Paco, start shooting!

51:48.523 --> 51:51.858
I don't like this. We should go.

51:52.277 --> 51:54.987
Let me handle this.

52:09.043 --> 52:11.795
- Get dressed! Get dressed!
- Okay.

52:12.046 --> 52:13.046
I said okay!

52:36.612 --> 52:38.322
Fuck!

52:47.498 --> 52:50.292
- Do you speak English?
- Yes.

52:50.460 --> 52:51.585
- Could you...?
- Yes, sir?

52:51.753 --> 52:52.836
I have a little problem.

52:53.046 --> 52:55.422
I need to know the number.
What number, please?

52:55.590 --> 52:57.174
Operation Desert Storm.

52:57.342 --> 52:59.134
I'm sorry? I need to know the number.

52:59.427 --> 53:01.720
The big Army in the desert.
It's an emergency.

53:01.971 --> 53:04.681
- You'll have to give me more specific...
- Fuck. Maybe...

53:08.478 --> 53:10.771
Come on, come on, come on.

53:24.327 --> 53:25.952
- Hello.
- Honey, it's me.

53:26.162 --> 53:27.371
Troy? Aah!

53:27.538 --> 53:31.124
Oh, my God! Oh, baby,
I was hoping it was you.

53:31.334 --> 53:34.294
- It's me, honey.
- Oh, God, the baby's crying.

53:34.462 --> 53:35.462
How's she doing?

53:35.671 --> 53:40.050
She hasn't slept good, and Mom had to
go back to work, so I'm real tired, baby.

53:40.301 --> 53:44.012
- I wish I was there to help, gooney bird.
- When are you coming home?

53:44.263 --> 53:46.223
Well, I'm working on that right now.

53:46.474 --> 53:49.559
I saw an ad for a computer job.
You want me to set up an interview?

53:49.811 --> 53:52.020
- Listen, honey...
- What date are you coming home?

53:52.271 --> 53:54.189
They haven't given us
an exact date yet...

53:54.440 --> 53:56.316
If I knew,
I could set up this interview...

53:56.567 --> 53:58.610
- Listen to me, please.
- What's happening?

53:59.987 --> 54:02.072
- What was that?
- The wall just exploded.

54:02.240 --> 54:03.490
I thought the war was over.

54:03.658 --> 54:06.243
It is and it isn't.
Could you call the reserve center?

54:06.411 --> 54:07.619
What do you want me to do?

54:07.870 --> 54:11.498
Tell the duty NCO I'm stuck in a bunker
near 223 north outside Karbala.

54:11.666 --> 54:14.751
Two-two-three north outside Karbala.

54:15.044 --> 54:18.004
- You're okay? Everything's okay?
- I don't want you to worry.

54:18.214 --> 54:20.841
I tried to do something
for the family, and....

54:21.092 --> 54:23.427
- I just want you to know...
- Know what?

54:23.636 --> 54:25.095
- I love you.
- What's going on?

54:25.263 --> 54:26.805
- Just tell Krystal.
- Troy.

54:28.182 --> 54:31.518
Tell Krystal I'm a rich man and if things
work out, she'll be taken care of.

54:31.686 --> 54:32.978
What are you talking about?

54:33.187 --> 54:36.189
- I gotta go, gooney bird! I love you!
- What's going on?

54:36.357 --> 54:38.900
Troy? Troy?

54:48.828 --> 54:51.079
Spirits are high
and the music is soaring...

54:51.330 --> 54:54.791
...as these young troops
celebrate the liberation of Kuwait.

54:55.042 --> 54:58.962
The mood here is boisterous and giddy,
as these troops are...

54:59.213 --> 55:02.090
I'm being held by a bunker outside...
Shit! Wait!

55:02.383 --> 55:06.970
I'm being held captive by Iraqi troops
outside a bunker near the gritty city...

55:07.221 --> 55:10.390
Cut, cut! You said "gritty city" again.

55:10.641 --> 55:13.768
Who gives a shit what I said?
These people are dying, for chrissake!

55:14.228 --> 55:17.939
- What about Private Wogaman, Adriana?
- Let's lay one down first.

55:18.149 --> 55:21.318
In three, two....
I'm being held captive by Iraqi troops....

55:21.736 --> 55:25.489
Okay. Okay. Okay.

55:25.656 --> 55:26.907
The rebels have gone down the road....

55:27.074 --> 55:28.074
Okay.

55:35.291 --> 55:39.211
Now, the assault, started by
the rebels from Karbala, came up on...

55:39.462 --> 55:41.505
Hey, back off! Hey, hey! No!

55:41.672 --> 55:44.424
- Sir, that's enough!
- We have a right to be here!

55:45.092 --> 55:46.259
That's mine.

55:46.427 --> 55:47.427
- Yes.
- No.

55:47.595 --> 55:49.429
Yes. Fuck it. Walter?

55:49.597 --> 55:51.973
- Could I have my pants, please?
- Walter?

55:52.141 --> 55:54.059
- My pants, on my legs.
- Go!

55:54.227 --> 55:55.936
Walter?

55:56.979 --> 55:59.022
- Go!
- Out! Get out!

56:01.359 --> 56:03.109
What did you wanna be as a little boy?

56:03.319 --> 56:07.280
As a boy, I wanted to be either
a veterinarian or a CIA sharpshooter.

56:07.448 --> 56:09.866
- Really? That's very complicated.
- Doug?

56:10.034 --> 56:11.409
Yes, colonel.

56:12.119 --> 56:15.288
- What the fuck are you doing?
- I'm giving an interview to NRG.

56:15.456 --> 56:18.333
- Do you have authorization?
- Yes, sir, I do.

56:23.798 --> 56:24.798
No.

56:24.966 --> 56:26.466
- No?
- No.

56:26.634 --> 56:28.260
- Who gave you this?
- Major Gates.

56:28.511 --> 56:32.222
Archie Gates gave you this?
Jesus Christ, Doug.

56:32.473 --> 56:35.976
- I don't get to do the interview?
- No, you don't get to do the interview.

56:36.143 --> 56:37.435
Come with me.

56:38.854 --> 56:42.566
Tell me where he is, or you're going
back to the hotel in Dhahran.

56:42.817 --> 56:45.277
I don't know. I think
he's helping Adriana Cruz.

56:45.528 --> 56:46.861
- Is she here?
- No, sir.

56:47.071 --> 56:48.363
So who else is missing?

56:48.531 --> 56:50.240
- Chief's not here.
- Chief's not here?

56:50.408 --> 56:52.826
You don't know where
your staff sergeant is, captain?

56:52.994 --> 56:54.578
Barlow and Vig are gone too, sir.

56:54.829 --> 56:57.789
They got a document
out of a guy's ass yesterday, sir.

56:58.624 --> 56:59.666
What?

56:59.834 --> 57:03.587
I don't know what it was. Some map
or secret list. But I saw it happen.

57:03.838 --> 57:06.006
- Did they bring it to you?
- No, sir.

57:06.465 --> 57:08.466
Yeah, see, he's working something.

57:08.843 --> 57:10.844
Get me some maps.
Check radio transmissions.

57:11.012 --> 57:12.929
Maybe we'll get their positions.

58:17.995 --> 58:20.830
What's wrong with him? Is he dead?

58:21.082 --> 58:23.750
Is that guy dead?
Where are you gonna put him?

58:24.168 --> 58:25.919
A shrine.

58:26.128 --> 58:28.755
A shrine? What kind of shrine y'all got?

58:28.923 --> 58:30.465
A shrine near a holy man...

58:30.883 --> 58:34.469
...that gives him comfort
and access to paradise.

58:35.971 --> 58:39.224
Hey, that sounds like
a pretty good shrine, right, chief?

58:40.393 --> 58:43.061
I'm not kidding.
It sounds like a good shrine.

58:45.856 --> 58:47.774
Hey, man, I'm sorry I hit you.

58:48.150 --> 58:51.611
I was just worried about Troy,
you know. He's my friend.

58:52.113 --> 58:53.863
I didn't want nothing
to happen to him.

58:54.615 --> 58:58.785
He's gonna take me to Detroit
with him, hook me up with a job.

58:59.078 --> 59:00.578
Come on, man. Chief.

59:05.418 --> 59:07.460
I know you was coming to help me.

59:14.176 --> 59:16.052
Thanks. I don't wanna hold no grudges.

59:16.929 --> 59:19.639
You got kicked out of that
ring of Jesus fire, huh?

59:19.807 --> 59:21.808
That ain't how it work.

59:22.893 --> 59:24.185
How's it work?

59:24.478 --> 59:27.814
I take care of whatever he puts
in front of me, no questions asked.

59:28.065 --> 59:30.734
He put that gold in front of me,
and I took it.

59:31.026 --> 59:32.902
That's how it works.

59:33.195 --> 59:34.988
What about now?

59:35.614 --> 59:37.991
I don't know. I gotta see.

59:40.995 --> 59:44.247
- How you doing, Conrad?
- I'm fine.

59:48.002 --> 59:49.377
It was my choice today.

59:50.337 --> 59:53.965
You can try and head back if you want.
Take your share and bury it.

59:54.216 --> 59:56.551
I'll find Barlow myself.

59:58.345 --> 01:00:00.180
I wanna find Troy.

01:00:00.347 --> 01:00:02.432
I'm here. I'm ready.

01:00:08.481 --> 01:00:10.607
Let's check the suitcases.

01:00:17.990 --> 01:00:19.449
I count 79.

01:00:19.700 --> 01:00:22.368
That means we're missing 41 bags.

01:00:22.661 --> 01:00:25.079
That's about $23 million left.

01:00:25.372 --> 01:00:30.084
Not bad for a disaster, provided we find
Barlow and not get court-martialed.

01:00:30.878 --> 01:00:32.253
How is she?

01:00:32.421 --> 01:00:35.173
Hey. How is your little girl?

01:00:36.383 --> 01:00:39.135
She's traumatized.
What do you expect?

01:00:40.554 --> 01:00:43.598
I went to B-school
at Bowling Green, okay?

01:00:43.766 --> 01:00:46.893
I came back to open
a couple of hotels near Karbala.

01:00:47.102 --> 01:00:49.896
I'm nearly in the black
when this stupid war starts...

01:00:50.064 --> 01:00:52.398
...and you guys bomb all my cafs.

01:00:52.733 --> 01:00:54.400
Now we try to get rid of Saddam...

01:00:54.568 --> 01:00:58.404
...Bush leaves us twisting in the winds.
Unbelievable.

01:01:02.618 --> 01:01:05.245
Look at these people.
Where is America now?

01:01:05.538 --> 01:01:07.121
Where is the Army now?

01:01:11.335 --> 01:01:12.961
- Do you have a radio?
- No.

01:01:13.128 --> 01:01:14.921
No radio, no water.

01:01:16.006 --> 01:01:18.758
- Where's Barlow?
- They got him.

01:01:19.176 --> 01:01:20.426
Where would they take him?

01:01:20.594 --> 01:01:23.638
Oasis bunker.
It's full of Saddam's Republican Guard.

01:01:23.931 --> 01:01:26.766
- Where's that?
- Approximately 17, 18 miles from here.

01:01:26.976 --> 01:01:28.977
- Take us there.
- We have no transportation.

01:01:29.228 --> 01:01:32.856
- We'll walk till we find some.
- Why don't you call in the Marines?

01:01:33.065 --> 01:01:35.233
- With what? We don't have a radio.
- Okay.

01:01:35.484 --> 01:01:39.946
We'll find a vehicle, you drive back,
get a helicopter, fly in, get your man.

01:01:40.155 --> 01:01:42.824
- We can't do that.
- Why not? You have a huge Army here.

01:01:43.075 --> 01:01:44.951
We shouldn't be involved
in the uprising.

01:01:45.119 --> 01:01:48.496
We killed Iraqi soldiers,
broke the peace accord.

01:01:48.831 --> 01:01:50.123
You know what I think?

01:01:50.457 --> 01:01:54.502
You're stealing gold. We're fighting Saddam
and dying, and you're stealing gold.

01:01:55.462 --> 01:01:56.671
You're wrong.

01:01:56.964 --> 01:01:58.756
They have half a million men here.

01:01:59.008 --> 01:02:02.343
They send four guys
to pick up all this bullion?

01:02:02.636 --> 01:02:04.178
I don't think so.

01:02:06.181 --> 01:02:09.893
We need to find our man.
How much do you want to take us to him?

01:02:10.644 --> 01:02:13.313
Is this still yours to give? Huh?

01:02:13.480 --> 01:02:16.983
The only reason you have these bags
is my people picked them up.

01:02:17.526 --> 01:02:19.068
We'll take our share...

01:02:19.320 --> 01:02:21.988
...and we will help you
carry your share.

01:02:23.240 --> 01:02:25.241
And find our man.

01:02:28.787 --> 01:02:29.871
Amir Abdulah.

01:02:31.582 --> 01:02:32.999
Archie Gates.

01:02:33.500 --> 01:02:36.419
- You'll take us to the Iranian border.
- What?

01:02:36.587 --> 01:02:40.214
If we don't get to a refugee camp,
we are dead. The nearest is in Iran.

01:02:40.424 --> 01:02:42.175
You don't need us. Buy your way.

01:02:42.343 --> 01:02:45.261
No. Saddam's soldiers
will never take Saddam's gold.

01:02:45.512 --> 01:02:47.764
Our only chance
is if we are with Americans.

01:02:48.015 --> 01:02:51.309
- We can't take you to the Iranian border.
- Then we don't have a deal.

01:02:51.477 --> 01:02:54.103
- Give me a fucking break, man.
- We just saved your life!

01:02:54.313 --> 01:02:56.564
- And we saved yours.
- We lost a man for you.

01:02:56.815 --> 01:02:59.984
What good is it if you leave us here
to be slaughtered, huh?

01:03:00.152 --> 01:03:04.447
The big Army of democracy beats the ugly
dictator and saves the rich Kuwaitis...

01:03:04.698 --> 01:03:09.327
...but you go to jail if you help us
escape the same dictator?

01:03:12.539 --> 01:03:14.540
You saw what happened to my wife.

01:03:15.417 --> 01:03:16.709
Look at my daughter.

01:03:21.340 --> 01:03:22.465
Who's going?

01:03:22.841 --> 01:03:25.218
Everyone but the priests. That makes 55.

01:03:38.691 --> 01:03:40.775
Did we save anything from the Humvee?

01:03:40.943 --> 01:03:44.237
Yeah. Vig's bag.

01:03:49.743 --> 01:03:50.785
Lovely.

01:03:53.580 --> 01:03:55.248
What is your rank, bro?

01:03:55.582 --> 01:03:57.166
Sergeant first class.

01:03:57.418 --> 01:03:58.918
Your company?

01:03:59.378 --> 01:04:02.505
437 Civil Affairs Company,
U.S. Army Reserve.

01:04:05.759 --> 01:04:06.759
My main man...

01:04:07.761 --> 01:04:10.096
...tell me something, okay?

01:04:11.098 --> 01:04:13.641
What is the problem
with Michael Jackson?

01:04:15.102 --> 01:04:16.477
What do you mean?

01:04:16.729 --> 01:04:20.106
What is the problem
with Michael Jackson?

01:04:23.110 --> 01:04:28.072
What is the problem
with Michael Jackson?

01:04:28.240 --> 01:04:30.533
You understand my question?

01:04:31.910 --> 01:04:33.119
No, I'm not sure I do.

01:04:33.287 --> 01:04:37.165
The King of Pop. Woo-hoo. Hee, hee.

01:04:37.458 --> 01:04:38.624
Yeah, Michael Jackson.

01:04:38.792 --> 01:04:41.461
He come to Egypt.
I see picture in newspaper.

01:04:41.670 --> 01:04:45.381
"Hello," with the white glove.
"I'm Michael Jackson in my hotel room...

01:04:45.632 --> 01:04:50.011
...with my chop-up face."
Your country make him chop up his face.

01:04:50.262 --> 01:04:51.637
I don't think so.

01:04:51.805 --> 01:04:55.183
Michael Jackson is pop king
of sick fucking country.

01:04:55.350 --> 01:04:57.560
That's bullshit. He did it to himself.

01:05:01.940 --> 01:05:05.359
You are the blind bullshit, my main man.

01:05:05.527 --> 01:05:07.779
It is so obvious a black man...

01:05:08.030 --> 01:05:11.657
...make the skin white and the hair
straight, and you know why?

01:05:11.867 --> 01:05:13.284
No.

01:05:13.452 --> 01:05:16.996
Your sick fucking country
make the black man hate himself...

01:05:17.164 --> 01:05:20.792
...just like you hate the Arab
and the children you bomb over here.

01:05:21.043 --> 01:05:22.668
I don't hate children.

01:05:22.836 --> 01:05:26.005
- This is illegal. The war's over.
- That's why you are illegal.

01:05:26.298 --> 01:05:29.342
You broke the ceasefire,
and I think maybe even you steal the gold.

01:05:29.593 --> 01:05:33.179
So nobody know where you are, right?
Your Army don't know.

01:05:33.347 --> 01:05:37.433
I'm gonna send you to Baghdad
for a long time. Nobody found you.

01:05:41.855 --> 01:05:44.190
- Do they care, buddy?
- Does who care?

01:05:44.358 --> 01:05:47.819
Do your Army care about the children
in Iraq? Do they come back to help?

01:05:48.278 --> 01:05:50.655
No, they're not coming.

01:06:04.211 --> 01:06:06.254
Do your Army...

01:06:06.421 --> 01:06:08.589
- ...come back to help the people?
- No.

01:06:09.258 --> 01:06:11.259
Tell the truth, dude-ski.

01:06:11.426 --> 01:06:13.261
Save us the big bummer.

01:06:13.512 --> 01:06:15.221
That's the truth.

01:06:45.961 --> 01:06:47.420
Does it hurt?

01:06:49.047 --> 01:06:51.632
I asked you a question, man.
Does it hurt?

01:06:51.925 --> 01:06:53.426
Yes, it hurts.

01:06:54.845 --> 01:06:57.471
You bomb my family. Do you know that?

01:06:58.891 --> 01:07:02.101
You blow up my home. The whole street.

01:07:02.352 --> 01:07:05.813
My wife is crushed by
big fucking block of concrete.

01:07:06.356 --> 01:07:08.274
She lose her legs.

01:07:08.609 --> 01:07:11.152
Those legs cut off now.

01:07:11.945 --> 01:07:13.779
- That's horrible.
- What?

01:07:14.781 --> 01:07:16.407
I said that's horrible.

01:07:16.575 --> 01:07:20.578
